er illuminating insights into the films and culture of the postwar years and provide a unique perspective on this eminent émigré intellectual.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMotion picturesvReviews. 0aMotion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  a1950s america.  a20th century.  aamerican and european cinema.  abiographical novels.  abook club reads.  abooks for movie lovers.  acinema trends.  adifferences in american and european film.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  afilm and cinema.  afilm critic books.  afilm history.  afilm theory.  agifts for friends.  ahistory of cinema.  ahistory.  ahow to be a movie critic.  alearning while reading.  aleisure reads.  apage turner.  aperforming arts.  apolitical trends in film.  apostwar history.  asiegfried kracauer.  aspeakeasy.  avacation reads.  awalter benjamin.1 aJay, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRawson, Kristy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 avon Moltke, Johannes, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095200340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520952003423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520952003/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles